     <h2>Our Mission</h2>
     <p>At The Donor Hub, our mission is to bridge the gap between blood donors and recipients by providing a comprehensive, user-friendly platform where lifesaving connections can be made quickly and easily. We are dedicated to fostering a community of generous donors, supporting blood banks, and facilitating efficient blood donation processes to save lives.
     </p>
 
     <hr>
 
     <h2>What We Do</h2>
     <p>The Donor Hub is designed to connect those in need of blood with willing donors and blood banks. Our platform offers several key features:
 
         <ul>
             <li>
                 <p>Donor Registration: Donors can create accounts, update their profiles, and make themselves available for donation requests.
                 </p>
             </li>
             <li>
                 <p>
                     Recipient Search: Recipients can search for and request donations from registered donors in their area.
                 </p>
             </li>
             <li>
                 <p>
                     Blood Bank Information: Blood banks can create profiles to display their details, including location, services, and contact information, making it easier for recipients to find and contact them.
                 </p>
             </li>
             <li>
                 <p>
                     Blood Camp Advertisements: Camp organizers can apply to advertise their events, and donors can search for the nearest blood donation camps to participate in.
                 </p>
             </li>
         </ul>
     </p>
 
    <hr>
 
     <h2>Our Vision</h2>
     <p>
         We envision a world where no one has to suffer due to a lack of blood. By leveraging technology and community, The Donor Hub aims to ensure that everyone in need has access to the life-saving blood they require, anytime and anywhere.
     </p>
 
     <hr>
 
     <h2>How It Works</h2>
     <ul>
         <li>
             <p>
                 For Donors: Create an account, fill out your donation eligibility details, and become available to be contacted by recipients in need.
             </p>
         </li>
         <li>
             <p>
                 For Recipients: Search for donors based on blood type and location, and send direct requests for blood donations.
             </p>
         </li>
         <li>
             <p>
                 For Blood Banks: Register your blood bank, update your profile with essential information, and connect with those in need.
             </p>
         </li>
         <li>
             <p>
                 For Camp Organizers: Advertise your blood donation camps to reach more potential donors and ensure successful events.
             </p>
         </li>
     </ul>
 
